<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id2063165">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id2063167"><p id="fs-id2063168">Which statement is true concerning the knee joint?</p>
<ol id="fs-id1649316" type="a">
<li>The lateral meniscus is an intrinsic ligament located on the lateral side of the knee joint.</li>
<li>Hyperextension is resisted by the posterior cruciate ligament.</li>
<li>The anterior cruciate ligament supports the knee when it is flexed and weight bearing.</li>
<li>The medial meniscus is attached to the tibial collateral ligament.</li>
</ol>
